na affair|Festina]] trial.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:silver;\" |  3 || nowrap | {{flagathlete|[[Fernando Escart\u00edn]]|ESP}} || Kelme || align=right| +10' 26\" || Named as a client of [[Francesco Conconi]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Tavshedens Pris og Danskerl\u00e6gen |language=Danish |publisher=DR |location=Denmark |url=http://www.dr.dk/Sporten/Dokumentar/Doping/20050530140756.htm |accessdate=18 October 2012}}</ref> Client of [[Michele Ferrari]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;background:red\"|  4 || nowrap | {{flagathlete|[[Laurent Dufaux]]|SUI}} || Saeco || align=right| +14' 43\"|| Sanctioned for doping during [[Festina affair]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;background:silver;\"|  5 || nowrap | {{flagathlete|[[\u00c1ngel Casero]]|ESP}} || Vitalicio Seguros || align=right| +15' 11\"|| Implicated in [[Operaci\u00f3n Puerto doping case|Operaci\u00f3n Puerto]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;background:red\"|  6 || nowrap | {{flagathlete|[[Abraham Olano]]|ESP}} || ONCE || align=right| +16' 47\" || Failed tests for Caffeine and suspended for 3 months in 1994. Named as a client of [[Francesco Conconi]] in the 1998 Giardini Margherita investigation.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.cyclingrevealed.com/Nov12/TdFChamps_Info.html |title=Tour de France Top 10 (1998 to 2012) |work=Cycling Revealed |year=2012 |accessdate=9 July 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;background:white;\"|  7 || nowrap | {{flagathlete|[[Daniele Nardello]]|ITA}} || Mapei || align=right| +17' 02\" ||\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;background:red\"|  8 || nowrap | {{flagathlete|[[Richard Virenque]]|FRA}} || Polti || align=right| +17' 28\"|| Sanctioned for doping during the [[Festina affair]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;background:white;\"|  9 || nowrap | {{flagathlete|[[Wladimir Belli]]|ITA}} || Festina || align=right| +17' 37\" ||\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;background:white;\"|  10 || nowrap | {{flagathlete|[[Andrea Peron (cyclist, born 1971)|Andrea Peron]]|ITA}} || ONCE || align=right| +23' 10\" ||\n|}\n\n=== 2000 Tour de France ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin-bottom:0;\"\n|-\n!Rank\n!Name\n!Team\n!Time\n!Notes\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:black;color:white\" |  1 || nowrap | {{flagathlete|[[Lance Armstrong]]|USA}} || nowrap |US Postal Service || align=right nowrap| 92h 33' 08\" || See [[#1999 Tour de France]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;background:red\"|  2 || nowrap | {{flagathlete|[[Jan Ullrich]]|GER}} || Telekom || align=right| +6' 02\"|| See [[#1998 Tour de France]]\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center; background:silver;\" |  3 || nowrap | {{flagathlete|[[Joseba Beloki]]|ESP}} || Festina || align=right| +10' 04\"||Implicated in the [[Operaci\u00f3n Puerto doping case]]. Name later removed from the case by Spanish officials in 2006.\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;background:red\"|  4 || nowrap | {{flagathlete|[[Christophe Moreau]]|FRA}} || Festina || align=right| +10' 34\"|| Failed tests for anabolic steroids in 1998.<ref>{{cite news|title=Masseur at centre of drugs find is linked to Virenque |newspaper=Irish Examiner |url=http://archives.tcm.ie/irishexaminer/1998/07/13/fshead.htm |accessdate=8 July 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929151117/http://archives.tcm.ie/irishexaminer/1998/07/13/fshead.htm |archivedate=29 September 2007  }}</ref> Admitted to taking EPO during the [[Festina affair|Festina]] trial.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tour riders down wheels over drug use |publisher=London independent |url=http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4158/is_19980725/ai_n14163112 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090511010226/http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4158/is_19980725/ai_n14163112/ |url-status=dead |archive-date=11 May 2009 |accessdate=28 July 2007}}</ref>\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;background:red\"|  5 || nowrap | {{flagathlete|[[Roberto Heras]]|ESP}} || Kelme || align=right | +11' 50\"  || Tested positive for EPO at the [[2